If ` X ` and ` Y ` are decomposed into two groups of digits of length ` M ` (only the lower group is known to be this size but the algorithm is most efficient when the partition is chosen near the middle of the digit string), then ` X Y ` can be written in three groups of digits, where each group needs only one multiplication.
